==English==
===Etymology===
French [[sans-culotte]], from [[sans]] 'without' + [[culotte]] 'breeches'

===Noun===
{{en-noun}} 
# person who lacks culture and [[refinement]]
# [[lower class]] person
# in 1792, the French [[aristocrat]]s, who wore fashionable [[breeches]], applied the term to their despised extremist adversaries in the [[French Revolution]], who had symbolically switched to [[pantaloons]] and soon adopted the term
# generalized to any radical or even violent [[extremist]] in politics

